<component><class>org.concord.modeler.PageTextBox</class>
<width>300.0</width>
<height>500.0</height>
<title>&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body face=&quot;verdana&quot;&gt;
    &lt;b&gt;About the model:&lt;/b&gt; The box contains some water molecules and there is 
    a gravitational field that always points downward. Investigate how the 
    molecules move when you rotate the box.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Instruction:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. 
    Press the &amp;quot;Run&amp;quot; button.&lt;br&gt;2. Drag the mouse inside the model&apos;s 
    window to rotate the box.&lt;br&gt;3. After every rotation, let the model run 
    for a while and observe the behavior of the molecules.&lt;br&gt;4. Pull the 
    &amp;quot;Temperature&amp;quot; slider to increase the temperature of the system, and repeat 
    2 and 3.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The simulation shows that in the liquid state, the water 
    molecules will always fill the bottom of the box, regardless of how you 
    rotate it, whereas in the gaseous state, they can be found everywhere. 
    This is what you observe in every day life.
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</title>
<opaque>false</opaque>
</component></content>

